<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Well, I have been reading the posts for weeks now, months even.  I seen lots of arguements about what a monk does and doesnt get, Armor complaints etc....and recently the weapon debate.  Well I have one simple statement to make:  How does placing a heavy arsed stick in my hands make me faster then my WEIGHTLESS fists?  hmmmm, let me say that again cause it really gets my goat:  WHY ARE MY FISTS SO DAMN SLOW!  They are slower then the big heavy Minotaur axe until lvl 25!  What is up...have u ever seen a Martial artist punch 1 in say 3 seconds?  No.  Now I know our dmg is hi, but only at later lvls.  I would prefer the monks fists to be a wee bit faster at lower lvls.  I mean when u start off, our bare hand is worse then a busted up club....now granted it should not do as much damage, but to be that slow too?!  No wonder people are turning to weapons.  There is no pride in having a slow attack.  WE are swift dealers of death via punching power.  But, we are no so until we either obtain a haste item or reach lvl 60 (which I am totally in awe of 14/26, that is the speed i ask for)  Now....I am not here to say use weapons, dont use weapons. I say to each their own, but I truly think u would have much more class respect if we werent so damn slow until lvl 40 (I just hit 42, and I did not like my dly one bit till recently)  I never stopped playing casue I enjoy the challenge of being a monk.  And that right there is reason enough to rebutt my arguement no doubt, I am just bringing to light a issue that has haunted me ever since I entered the world for the first day as the Clown Prince of Pugilism (who wields a Fighting Baton in his off hand in case someone orders the salad:)<br>
ENjoy your path in Norrath and remember: The grass is just as green on your side as it is on the other; you just need to water more!<br>
Have fun and safe journies!</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
