<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Yes the delay of fists is far too high, even higher than daggers.  However, when you watch a boxing match, you will see that a combo might be fast, but there is a lot of waiting in between, waiting for a good opening.  Even in martial arts, you might strike kick strike, then you gain your balance, turn to face the enemy again, etc.<p>

This might be stretching it, but a person with a dagger just kinda flails around with it, not too concerned about accuracy.  A dagger should be heavier than a fist though, thats for sure.<p>

If you want realism, EQ has very little.  Fact is one good hit with a just about any weapon, and that guy is down.  Against plate?  maybe not, but I havent fought anything in EQ with plate recently.  A well placed dagger can kill with one hit, as well as an arrow.<br>
The whole idea of hit points is just absurd.  But hey, its a game.<p>

-Rellin Quickfists</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
