<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Ok, I will admit right off this is way off topic, but I just had to point out some flaws in Spektyr's argument.<p>

You are dead wrong about a swordsman just flailing around with his sword as opposed to a martial artist doing the same with is fist. Anyone with an ounce of sword training would know that you DO NOT take wild swings with a sword, because it throws yuo off balance and leaves you totally open to counterattack if you miss, resulting in a quick defeat (or death.) Conversely, it takes a good deal of time studying hand-to-hand combat before the instinct to swing wildly with your fists gives way to controlled, smooth punches and strikes. if you need proof, just visit a beginner's martial arts class. Also, as for your example of the martial artist confronted by the swordsman, forget what you've seen in movies and TV. The fighter's first priority would be to flee. He'd know enough not to face a sword unless there was no avenue for escape, and then his main objective would be to incapacitate the swordsman enough to escape, or disarm him and use the sword himself, not wait like an idiot for the swordsman to do something even dumber and then do his "body part rearranging" moves.<p>

BTW- I love your term "monkly combat." I think mostly cuz it makes me think of "monkey combat," but I digress even further.<p>

Anyhoo, it would be nice for fists to be faster, but then that would just be ridiculous when you got to higher levels and you were throwing chains of deathblows on every turn. Yeah it would look cool, but that would totally unbalance things. The truth of the matter is, ALL of the combat systems are flawed if you compare them to real life. Verant has done a remarkable job as is with the combat system. If you disagree, go check out Asheron's Call. You will come back to EQ without another complaint ever. Maybe one day we'll have an RPG with near-realistic combat (trust me, you don't want total realism. It is pretty ugly), and I'll be first in line to play. Until then, just be thankful for what we have now.<hr>Nazrael (Dark Elf ShadowKnight) / Garthak (Human Monk)<br>
Destroyer of Dreams<br>
Torvonnilous</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
