<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I just want to defend Spektyrs argument about why fists are slow.  <p>

Of course someone isn't going into battle just swinging like crazy but I believe what he was saying is that with your fists you have to get in closer combat, putting you at greater risk.  You also can't block a sword nearly as easily with your arm as with a steel weapon.  So you ARE more cautious when going in with your fists, waiting for an opening to get in close.  I'm no martial artest or anything but make a couple wooden swords and try it out.<p>

And BTW if you look at it from a game designers point of view there are reasons they made them like that.  How would you like to have twice the taunting power while you are doing the same damage.  No warrior could get the mob off of you...  If you want realism wait 50 years and you'll see some really realistic games...  But with limited computer power you can't write code for everything and sometimes things aren't exactly how we would like them to be.  But the programmers do their best.  So if you talk about wanting faster fists do it as a dream.  Don't complain that Verant didn't do a good job.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
